 succeeded in 1306ms:
Dataset ds001_crc analysis summary

Decoded 50000 records from dataset.parquet. Outcome pfs_months ranged from 0.00 to 16.25, with median 4.21 and IQR 2.72-5.74. Analyses used mean differences and linear regression coefficients on the natural month scale; p-values use large-sample normal approximations for t statistics.

Main clinical status effects: Stage IV disease and worse ECOG performance status were strongly associated with shorter PFS. Stage IV patients had lower mean PFS by 1.35 months, and each ECOG point was associated with -1.19 months.

Tumor biology: BRAF V600E and right-sided primary tumors were adverse in unadjusted analyses, while MSI-high status was favorable. KRAS mutation was also adverse. In the interaction analyses, BRAF with right-sided primary and MSI with right-sided primary were tested to probe biologic heterogeneity.

Treatments: Pembrolizumab, cetuximab, bevacizumab, encorafenib, and trastuzumab/tucatinib showed positive adjusted treatment coefficients, while regorafenib was negative. The biomarker-matched hypotheses were most supported for pembrolizumab in MSI-high disease, encorafenib in BRAF V600E disease, and HER2-targeted treatment in HER2-amplified disease, based on positive interaction/subgroup estimates where applicable.

Inflammation, nutrition, and disease burden: Higher albumin was favorable, while LDH, CRP, NLR, CEA, alkaline phosphatase, liver metastases, and bone metastases were adverse. Several of these remained significant in the multivariable model, indicating that the lab and metastatic burden signals were not only proxies for stage/performance status.

Comorbidities: Heart failure and chronic kidney disease were associated with shorter unadjusted PFS. Pembrolizumab-treated patients with autoimmune disease had lower mean PFS, and the pembrolizumab-by-autoimmune interaction tested whether immune-related comorbidity modified treatment benefit.

The full multivariable model included 36 predictors and achieved R-squared 0.842. The most statistically prominent adjusted coefficients included: age_years 0.18 months, ecog_ps -1.17 months, stage_iv -1.36 months, treatment_regorafenib 0.94 months, albumin_g_dl 0.47 months, kras_mutation -0.36 months, right_sided_primary -0.28 months, cea_ng_ml -0.00 months, braf_v600e -0.36 months, ldh_u_l -0.00 months, copd -0.03 months, nlr 0.00 months.

Overall, the cohort shows coherent colorectal cancer patterns: advanced stage, poor performance status, inflammatory/nutritional derangement, metastatic burden, and adverse molecular features predict shorter PFS, while biomarker-aligned targeted or immune therapy is associated with longer PFS in the corresponding molecular subgroups.

